(Lucas crying)

11:18.792 --> 11:21.041
OH. COULD WE PAUSE
FOR A MOMENT, PLEASE.

11:21.083 --> 11:23.041
HERE. I'LL GET IT.
I'LL GET HIM.
YEAH?

11:23.083 --> 11:24.375
YEAH.

11:29.083 --> 11:33.333
I SHOULD GET OUTTA HERE
AND GO PICK UP VANESSA.

11:33.375 --> 11:34.834
(Amelia) VANESSA?

11:34.875 --> 11:37.583
HIS GIRLFRIEND.

11:37.625 --> 11:39.041
YEAH. (chuckles)
THANK YOU.

11:39.083 --> 11:41.625
UH, ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

11:41.667 --> 11:43.500
SEE YOU.
HAVE FUN. HAVE FUN.

11:45.000 --> 11:47.041
(sighs)

11:47.083 --> 11:49.792
OKAY, SO YOU AND SAM...

11:49.834 --> 11:51.583
WHAT IS WITH THE TENSION?

11:51.625 --> 11:53.750
THERE'S NO TENSION.
I WAS SITTING RIGHT HERE.

11:53.792 --> 11:57.000
I MEAN,
YOU BARELY LOOKED AT HIM.

12:01.250 --> 12:03.000
THERE WAS A THING.

12:03.041 --> 12:05.458
WITH YOU AND SAM?
WITH ME AND SAM.

12:05.500 --> 12:07.458
AND NAOMI DID NOT
TAKE IT WELL.

12:07.500 --> 12:10.458
AND NOW I'M WITH PETE, AND SAM
IS WITH VANESSA, AND IT'S FINE.

12:10.500 --> 12:13.041
IT'S VERY ADULT.
SOUNDS VERY MESSY.

12:13.083 --> 12:15.458
NO, IT'S NOT, ACTUALLY.
IT'S GREAT.

12:15.500 --> 12:17.500
MY LIFE IS WORKING.

12:17.542 --> 12:19.000
ADDISON.

12:19.041 --> 12:20.709
(glass clatters on table)

12:20.750 --> 12:23.208
I MEAN, THIS IS ME
YOU'RE TALKING TO.

12:23.250 --> 12:25.917
I CAUGHT YOU WITH
MY BROTHER'S BEST FRIEND

12:25.959 --> 12:27.667
AND I KEPT YOUR SECRET.

12:27.709 --> 12:29.667
I MEAN, YOU CAN TALK TO ME.

12:29.709 --> 12:33.000
YOU USED TO TRUST ME.

12:33.041 --> 12:34.667
I CHOSE PETE.

12:34.709 --> 12:37.041
I CHOOSE PETE.
HE'S GREAT. WE'RE GREAT.

12:37.083 --> 12:40.041
AND... I CAN'T HAVE KIDS,

12:40.083 --> 12:42.500
AND PETE HAS LUCAS.

12:42.542 --> 12:44.709
SO THAT'S SORT OF THIS...

12:44.750 --> 12:46.709
AMAZING ICING ON THE CAKE.

12:46.750 --> 12:48.250
EXCEPT FOR THE FACT THAT...

12:48.291 --> 12:50.500
PETE'S STILL IN LOVE
WITH LUCAS' MOTHER,

12:50.542 --> 12:53.041
WHICH IS...

12:53.083 --> 12:57.041
OH, ADDIE.

12:57.083 --> 13:00.208
SO ANYWAY... CHEERS.

13:00.250 --> 13:02.333
(clink)

13:05.875 --> 13:07.250
I MISSED YOU.

13:09.375 --> 13:11.750
YOU KNOW, YOU WERE ALWAYS
A BETTER SISTER

13:11.792 --> 13:13.375
THAN THE ONES I HAD.

13:13.417 --> 13:16.458
AND YOU WERE WAY BETTER
THAN MY BROTHER.

13:16.500 --> 13:18.750
ARE THINGS OKAY
BETWEEN YOU TWO?

13:18.792 --> 13:22.166
HE'S THE GOLDEN CHILD.
(clears throat)

13:22.208 --> 13:24.500
EVERYTHING'S ALWAYS OKAY
WITH HIM.

13:27.375 --> 13:29.959
THAT WAS PAINFUL.

13:30.000 --> 13:31.959
AT LEAST THEY TOOK
SOME CONDOMS.

13:32.000 --> 13:35.000
AH, DO YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS
OR--OR WANT SOME MORE CONDOMS?

13:35.041 --> 13:37.959
ACTUALLY,
I DO HAVE A QUESTION

13:38.000 --> 13:40.333
FOR THE GENTLEMAN,
IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

13:40.375 --> 13:42.041
THE GENTLEMAN.

13:42.083 --> 13:44.125
OF COURSE.

13:44.166 --> 13:46.208
I'LL BE WAITING.

13:50.750 --> 13:52.000
HELLO.

13:56.083 --> 13:59.041
HOW C--HOW CAN I... HELP?

13:59.083 --> 14:01.333
I DON'T REALLY KNOW
HOW TO SAY THIS.

14:01.375 --> 14:03.333
UH, IT'S SOMEWHAT
EMBARRASSING.

14:03.375 --> 14:06.625
NO, I'M--I'M--I'M A DOCTOR.
I'VE HEARD IT ALL.

14:06.667 --> 14:08.041
(whispers) COME...

14:08.083 --> 14:09.125
OKAY.

14:09.166 --> 14:12.750
WELL... NORA AND I...

14:12.792 --> 14:15.083
WE'VE BEEN DATING
FOR SEVERAL MONTHS.

14:15.125 --> 14:18.458
SHE'S A REALLY LOVELY WOMAN,
REALLY LOVELY.

14:18.500 --> 14:22.041
AND OUR, UH, OUR INTIMATE TIME
HAS BEEN VERY GOOD

14:22.083 --> 14:25.041
EXCEPT LATELY, IT'S BEEN
DIFFICULT FOR ME TO--

14:25.083 --> 14:27.041
OH, YOU KNOW,
AS MEN GET OLDER,

14:27.083 --> 14:30.041
IT'S, UH, IT'S VERY COMMON
FOR THEM TO HAVE DIFFICULTY,

14:30.083 --> 14:33.041
AS YOU SAY, GETTING, UM...
TRYING TO--

14:33.083 --> 14:35.041
NO, IT'S NOT THAT.
OH.

14:35.083 --> 14:37.375
I'M STILL ABLE TO PERFORM.
OH, GOOD. GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.

14:37.417 --> 14:40.375
IT'S JUST BECOME UNCOMFORTABLE.
MY PELVIS IS SORE.

14:40.417 --> 14:43.000
IT DOESN'T WANT TO MOVE
THE WAY IT USED TO.

14:43.041 --> 14:46.000
SO I DON'T FIND MYSELF
GETTING, UH, IN THE MOOD.

14:46.041 --> 14:47.041
OH.

14:47.083 --> 14:50.041
SO... I WAS HOPING
YOU WOULD HAVE SOME PILLS

14:50.083 --> 14:51.917
TO HELP WITH LIBIDO.

14:51.959 --> 14:53.166
GIVEN YOUR DISCOMFORT,

14:53.208 --> 14:55.166
I THINK YOU SHOULD HAVE
A COMPLETE EXAM

14:55.208 --> 14:57.291
BEFORE WE PRESCRIBE ANYTHING.

14:57.333 --> 15:00.500
AND YOU CAN DO THAT? I COULD
MAKE AN APPOINTMENT WITH YOU,

15:00.542 --> 15:03.083
AND YOU COULD CHECK ME OUT?
IT'S--IT'S MY ASSOCIATE'S
SPECIALTY NOT MINE.

15:03.125 --> 15:06.166
BUT I CAN BRING HER UP TO SPEED
ON EVERYTHING WE TALKED ABOUT.

15:06.208 --> 15:07.917
BUT YOU REALLY--

15:07.959 --> 15:10.917
YOU REALLY SHOULD MAKE
AN AP-APPOINTMENT TO SEE HER.

15:10.959 --> 15:14.041
WITH A LADY?

15:14.083 --> 15:16.083
SHE'S NO LADY.

15:20.542 --> 15:23.709
Y'ALL KEPT ME UP TILL
3:00 THIS MORNING.

15:23.750 --> 15:25.709
OH, OH, GOD. I'M SORRY.
NO, I'M JUST KIDDING.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.709
SORRY, SAM.
I'M GLAD SHE'S HERE.

15:27.750 --> 15:29.208
I--ME, TOO. IT'S NICE.

15:29.250 --> 15:34.041
I FORGOT... HOW MUCH I LIKE
HAVING SOMEONE TO TALK TO.

15:34.083 --> 15:37.041
(chuckles)

15:37.083 --> 15:38.834
YOU CAN TALK TO ME.

15:38.875 --> 15:41.083
NO, I CAN'T.

15:41.125 --> 15:42.041
IT--

15:42.083 --> 15:43.959
SAM, I CAN'T.

15:44.000 --> 15:47.458
I KNOW. OH, BOY.

15:49.083 --> 15:50.750
AMELIA?

15:50.792 --> 15:54.041
UH, EDDIE WANTED TO HEAR
MORE ABOUT THE SURGERY.

15:54.083 --> 15:57.041
SO WE STARTED TALKING,
AND ONE THING LED TO ANOTHER,

15:57.083 --> 15:59.125
AND, UH...

15:59.166 --> 16:01.750
AND WHAT?

16:01.792 --> 16:04.125
AND HE ASKED ME
TO DO THE SURGERY.

16:04.166 --> 16:06.041
AND I SAID YES.

16:11.625 --> 16:13.709
I CAN DO THE SURGERY
AND SAVE THE BABIES.

16:13.750 --> 16:16.333
I JUST NEED YOU IN THERE
TO KEEP AN EYE ON THEM

16:16.375 --> 16:18.583
AND SAM TO MAINTAIN
THE CARDIOVASCULAR FUNCTION.

16:18.625 --> 16:20.041
THIS CAN WORK.
IT'S RECKLESS.

16:20.083 --> 16:22.041
HOW--WELL, HOW--
HOW WOULD THIS WORK?

16:22.083 --> 16:25.333
JUST FOR EDDIE'S SAKE, I WANT
TO KNOW HOW THIS WOULD WORK.

16:25.375 --> 16:27.333
MM-HMM. I WOULD RELIEVE
THE OBSTRUCTION

16:27.375 --> 16:29.041
BY PLACING A STENT
IN THE AQUEDUCT,

16:29.083 --> 16:31.041
AND THEN
AS THE PRESSURE DROPS,

16:31.083 --> 16:33.291
THE ACTIVITY IN THE BRAIN STEM
WILL RETURN,

16:33.333 --> 16:36.041
AND KAYLA WAKES UP.
AND IF IT WORKS,
WHAT STATE WILL SHE BE IN?

16:36.083 --> 16:38.041
WILL SHE
BE ABLE TO FUNCTION?

16:38.083 --> 16:41.041
I DON'T KNOW. BUT IF WE DON'T
DO IT, WE WILL NEVER KNOW.

16:41.083 --> 16:43.959
I'M AGAINST THIS.
I AM, TOO.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.959
TWO NEUROSURGEONS SAID NO
TO THIS, ONE BEING YOUR MENTOR,

16:47.000 --> 16:49.709
THE OTHER BEING YOUR BROTHER.
DEREK LOOKED AT AN E-MAIL
OF A SCAN.

16:49.750 --> 16:51.709
I MEAN, HE--HE DIDN'T EVEN
SEE THE PATIENT,

16:51.750 --> 16:53.208
WHICH ULTIMATELY
DOESN'T MATTER,

16:53.250 --> 16:55.834
BECAUSE EDDIE LINDY MADE
A DECISION TO SAVE HIS WIFE.

16:55.875 --> 16:58.500
HE ASKED ME TO DO IT,
AND I CAN DO IT.

16:58.542 --> 17:00.625
NOW WILL YOU GIVE ME
PRIVILEGES HERE?

17:02.166 --> 17:03.417
YES.

17:03.458 --> 17:05.792
(Addison) GREAT.

17:05.834 --> 17:07.875
I'LL GET YOU AN O.R.
FOR TOMORROW.

17:10.041 --> 17:13.000
ADDISON, WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO TO STOP HER?

17:13.041 --> 17:15.208
NOTHING.
LOOK, I WAS WRONG.
I MADE A BAD CALL.

17:15.250 --> 17:18.208
YEAH, WELL... (chuckles)
I ADMIT THAT. BUT WE'RE BOTH
ON THE SAME SIDE WITH THIS.

17:18.250 --> 17:21.208
WE BOTH WANT TO GIVE
THOSE BABIES A CHANCE.
WHAT, DO YOU REALLY THINK
I CAN TALK HER OUT OF IT?

17:21.250 --> 17:24.208
I COULDN'T TALK YOU OUT OF IT.
I THINK YOU COULD TRY. I THINK
YOU COULD TRY TALKING TO HER.

17:24.250 --> 17:26.208
EDDIE WANTS THIS,
AMELIA IS SET,

17:26.250 --> 17:29.208
AND SHE JUST GOT SANCTIONED
BY THE CHIEF OF STAFF.

17:29.250 --> 17:32.583
YOU KNOW HER. YOU KNOW
THIS IS WRONG. SO STOP HER.

17:32.625 --> 17:34.041
(motor whirring)

17:34.083 --> 17:36.041
HAVE YOU REVIEWED
THE APPLICATION?

17:36.083 --> 17:38.875
NOT YET.
OVERNIGHT IT TO NAOMI.

17:38.917 --> 17:41.041
REALLY? YOU DON'T THINK
SHE HAS ENOUGH ON HER PLATE?

17:41.083 --> 17:44.083
WHY ARE YOU
ROLLING AROUND HERE

17:44.125 --> 17:46.041
WITH THIS GIGANTIC CHIP
ON YOUR SHOULDER?

17:46.083 --> 17:48.041
YOU SHOULD'VE NEVER TOLD ME
ABOUT WILLIAM'S A.L.S.

17:48.083 --> 17:49.458
YOU KNOW, I-I GET IT.

17:49.500 --> 17:51.917
YOU'RE UPSET THAT YOUR STUDY
ISN'T GOING FAST ENOUGH.

17:51.959 --> 17:54.709
I'LL READ THE APPLICATION,
I'LL GET--

17:54.750 --> 17:56.834
THIS ISN'T ABOUT
THE DAMN APPLICATION.

17:56.875 --> 17:59.041
I SLEPT WITH NAOMI.

17:59.083 --> 18:03.834
AND... THEN I TOLD HER
ABOUT WILLIAM.

18:03.875 --> 18:05.041
Y--

18:05.083 --> 18:06.500
YEAH, YEAH.

18:06.542 --> 18:08.041
YOU TOLD NAOMI...

18:08.083 --> 18:11.041
(lowered voice)
THAT WILLIAM HAS A.L.S.?

18:11.083 --> 18:14.083
WHY?

18:14.125 --> 18:16.500
I DON'T KNOW.

18:16.542 --> 18:18.959
(chuckles)
I WANTED MORE FROM HER,

18:19.000 --> 18:21.959
AND I THOUGHT IT WAS
THE RIGHT THING TO DO

18:22.000 --> 18:24.500
OR THAT SHE'D BE PISSED AT HIM
FOR WITHHOLDING.

18:24.542 --> 18:26.875
I DON'T KNOW.

18:26.917 --> 18:28.917
DOESN'T MATTER.

18:28.959 --> 18:30.458
SHE'S GONE.

18:30.500 --> 18:33.667
(motor whirring)

18:35.500 --> 18:40.041
PROSTATE CANCER?

18:40.083 --> 18:44.041
I CAME IN FOR LOSS OF LIBIDO,
PAIN FROM ARTHRITIS.

18:44.083 --> 18:46.041
(Charlotte) DISCOVERY
OF PROSTATE CANCER

18:46.083 --> 18:48.041
IS OFTEN
AN INCIDENTAL FINDING.

18:48.083 --> 18:50.041
YOU DON'T FIND IT
IF YOU DON'T LOOK,

18:50.083 --> 18:52.041
AND THEN IT'S TOO LATE.

18:52.083 --> 18:54.125
WHAT IS THE TREATMENT?

18:54.166 --> 18:57.041
IN YOUR CASE, I RECOMMEND
RADIATION THERAPY--

18:57.083 --> 18:58.583
EITHER EXTERNAL

18:58.625 --> 19:01.875
OR WITH AN IMPLANTABLE
RADIOACTIVE SEED.

19:01.917 --> 19:05.041
WHAT ABOUT...

19:05.083 --> 19:07.083
WHAT ABOUT MY JOHNSON?

19:07.125 --> 19:09.500
WILL IT STILL WORK AFTER?

19:09.542 --> 19:11.500
ABOUT HALF OF ALL PATIENTS

19:11.542 --> 19:13.542
DO EXPERIENCE
ERECTILE DIFFICULTY

19:13.583 --> 19:17.125
FOLLOWING RADIATION.
AND THERE ARE NO
ALTERNATIVE TREATMENTS?

19:17.166 --> 19:19.583
WELL, GIVEN YOUR CIRCUMSTANCES,
NOT THAT I RECOMMEND.

19:19.625 --> 19:22.125
BUT THERE ARE THINGS WE CAN DO
IF IMPOTENCE OCCURS

19:22.166 --> 19:24.959
AS A SIDE EFFECT
OF THE RADIATION--

19:25.000 --> 19:26.166
INJECTIONS, PUMPS--

19:26.208 --> 19:29.125
IF I DON'T HAVE
THE TREATMENT...

19:29.166 --> 19:31.166
HOW LONG DO I HAVE?

19:33.083 --> 19:36.000
FOUR, MAYBE FIVE YEARS.

19:41.083 --> 19:43.417
IT'S BEEN LOVELY
TALKING TO YOU.

19:43.458 --> 19:45.041
THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME.

19:45.083 --> 19:49.083
MR. SCHMITT.

19:49.125 --> 19:50.667
(Cooper) HE'S A MAN,

19:50.709 --> 19:52.041
AND YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT HIM
LOSING HIS MANHOOD.
I GET THAT.

19:52.083 --> 19:54.166
NO, YOU CAN'T. YOU'RE A WOMAN.
YOU COULDN'T POSSIBLY KNOW

19:54.208 --> 19:56.166
HOW SOMETHING LIKE THAT
WOULD MAKE HIM FEEL.

19:56.208 --> 19:58.625
AND YOU'RE A MAN,
SO OF COURSE YOU DO.

19:58.667 --> 20:00.166
YES, THAT'S RIGHT.

20:00.208 --> 20:03.166
I MEAN, IS THE GUY
EVEN MAKING THE WRONG DECISION?

20:03.208 --> 20:05.166
PROSTATE CANCER'S
PRETTY SLOW GROWING. HE'S 80.

20:05.208 --> 20:08.125
IF HE WANTS TO LIVE THE LIFE
HE HAS LEFT ON HIS OWN TERMS

20:08.166 --> 20:10.125
AND NOT HAVE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SEX,

20:10.166 --> 20:12.583
WHO ARE WE TO TELL HIM NO?
SO I SHOULD JUST LET HIM DIE?

20:12.625 --> 20:15.625
OH, COME ON.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I'M SAYING.
HE'S IN
EXTRAORDINARILY GOOD HEALTH.

20:15.667 --> 20:18.041
AND THIS CANCER'S AGGRESSIVE.
HIS GLEASON LEVEL'S A 7.

20:18.083 --> 20:21.041
AND IF HE'S MADE IT TO 80,

20:21.083 --> 20:23.667
STATISTICALLY, HE'S GOT A GOOD
SHOT OF MAKING IT TO 100.

20:23.709 --> 20:25.709
NOW HE'S GOT A WOMAN
THAT HE LOVES--

20:25.750 --> 20:27.709
THAT HE WANTS TO BE ABLE
TO LOVE.

20:27.750 --> 20:29.709
HE DOESN'T WANT TO BE
EMASCULATED, CHARLOTTE.

20:29.750 --> 20:32.041
IS IT SO HARD FOR YOU
TO SEE THAT?

20:32.083 --> 20:35.166
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT OSCAR
OR WE TALKING ABOUT YOU?

20:35.208 --> 20:37.000
EXCUSE ME?

20:37.041 --> 20:39.250
EMASCULATION SEEMS TO BE
YOUR CATCH PHRASE FOR ME.

20:39.291 --> 20:41.250
I WASN'T TALKING ABOUT YOU,
BUT TRUTH?

20:41.291 --> 20:43.709
YEAH, YOU LIKE TO BE TOUGHER
THAN EVERYONE ELSE,

20:43.750 --> 20:46.917
AND THAT MAKES
SOME PEOPLE PULL AWAY.
I THOUGHT WE WERE PAST THIS.

20:46.959 --> 20:48.709
YOU BROUGHT IT UP.

20:48.750 --> 20:51.000
I CAME TO YOU FOR HELP.

20:51.041 --> 20:54.750
WELL, MAYBE THAT WASN'T
SUCH A GOOD IDEA.
CLEARLY.

20:58.291 --> 21:00.166
(knocks on door)

21:00.208 --> 21:01.917
DR. SHEPHERD.

21:01.959 --> 21:05.041
UH, THIS IS
ANGIE AND SIMON McCONNELL.

21:05.083 --> 21:07.125
THEY'RE THE PARENTS THAT
KAYLA'S SURROGATE FOR.

21:07.166 --> 21:09.041
THEY WANTED TO MEET YOU.

21:09.083 --> 21:12.041
WELL, I'D--I'D SHAKE
YOUR HANDS, BUT...

21:12.083 --> 21:14.875
DR. MONTGOMERY TOLD US
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

21:14.917 --> 21:16.875
EDDIE DOESN'T WANT
TO HEAR THIS,

21:16.917 --> 21:20.041
BUT OUR BABIES
ARE BARELY VIABLE.

21:20.083 --> 21:22.417
HE'S WELL AWARE.
WE KNOW
THIS IS HORRIBLE TO ASK

21:22.458 --> 21:25.917
AFTER ALL THAT KAYLA'S
BEEN THROUGH, BUT...

21:25.959 --> 21:28.500
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

21:28.542 --> 21:31.500
WE ARE SO CLOSE
TO HAVING OUR FAMILY.

21:33.083 --> 21:36.000
WOULD YOU TALK WITH ME
OUTSIDE FOR A MINUTE?

21:42.166 --> 21:44.375
YOU THOUGHT IF I SAW THE PARENTS
WITH THEIR SAD FACES,

21:44.417 --> 21:45.959
WHAT, I WAS JUST
GONNA BACK DOWN?

21:46.000 --> 21:47.542
LOOK,
I'M DOING THE RIGHT THING.

21:47.583 --> 21:49.542
NOT FOR THE BABIES.
THE RISK IS TOO HIGH.

21:49.583 --> 21:51.542
THE ADDISON MONTGOMERY I KNOW
WOULD WADE THROUGH FIRE

21:51.583 --> 21:52.333
FOR A PATIENT.

21:52.375 --> 21:54.333
SHE WOULDN'T WHINE ABOUT
THE RISKS.

21:54.375 --> 21:55.583
I MEAN, SHE'D GO
ALL SUPER WOMAN ON ME

21:55.625 --> 21:57.333
TRYING TO CONVINCE ME
TO DO THE SURGERY.

21:57.375 --> 22:00.041
WHAT IS IT? WHAT, YOU'RE
SETTLING IN YOUR PERSONAL LIFE,

22:00.083 --> 22:03.041
SO NOW YOU'RE WILLING TO SETTLE
WITH YOUR PATIENTS, TOO?
I AM NOT SETTLING, AMELIA.

22:03.083 --> 22:04.959
YOU HAVE FEELINGS
FOR SOMEONE ELSE.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.041
PETE HAS FEELINGS
FOR HIS KID'S MOM.

22:07.083 --> 22:10.041
YOU SAY IT'S GREAT.
YOU DON'T SEEM GREAT.
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

22:10.083 --> 22:15.083
YOU SEEM SAD, ADDISON.
AND YOU SHOULD BE.

22:15.125 --> 22:17.166
OKAY, WHAT--YOU ARE WAY
OUT OF LINE HERE.

22:17.208 --> 22:19.166
YOU SHOULD WANT MORE...

22:19.208 --> 22:23.458
MORE FOR YOURSELF
AND MORE FOR KAYLA.

22:25.417 --> 22:28.125
(door closes)

22:31.417 --> 22:33.208
I CAN'T DECIDE
IF IT'S WORSE

22:33.250 --> 22:35.208
IF SHE CHOOSES WILLIAM
AND HE DIES

22:35.250 --> 22:37.291
OR IF SHE CHOOSES ME
AND HE LIVES.

22:37.333 --> 22:39.792
YOU DON'T WANT HIM
TO DIE.
RIGHT, RIGHT.

22:39.834 --> 22:43.625
'CAUSE THEN I GOTTA COMPETE
WITH HIS GHOST.
YEAH, BUT HE LIVES, YOU GOTTA
COMPETE WITH ALL THAT MONEY.

22:43.667 --> 22:46.000
IT'S LOSE-LOSE EITHER WAY,
RIGHT?
YES, WHICH IS WHY
WE'RE HERE. MOVE ON.

22:46.041 --> 22:47.667
MOVE ON.

22:47.709 --> 22:49.667
MOVE ON.

22:49.709 --> 22:52.041
(The Cribs)
♪ I'M A ROMANTIC ♪

22:52.083 --> 22:53.625
♪ I AM INDECISIVE ♪

22:53.667 --> 22:56.750
BRINGS US BACK
TO COOPER'S DILEMMA.

22:56.792 --> 22:59.750
WOULD YOU RATHER HAVE
10 TO 15 YEARS OF LIFE

22:59.792 --> 23:02.041
OR FOUR YEARS OF SEX?

23:02.083 --> 23:03.542
SEX.
SEX.
THAT'S NOT THE DILEMMA.

23:03.583 --> 23:06.041
THE DILEMMA IS HOW DO I CONTINUE
WORKING WITH CHARLOTTE KING?

23:06.083 --> 23:08.041
MAYBE THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE.

23:08.083 --> 23:11.041
MAYBE IT'S YOU
WHO NEEDS TO MOVE ON.
NO, I ALREADY MOVED ON
FROM CHARLOTTE.

23:11.083 --> 23:14.625
I JUST CAN'T MOVE AWAY FROM HER
AND HER EMASCULATING WAYS.

23:14.667 --> 23:16.166
RIGHT, RIGHT,

23:16.208 --> 23:18.166
'CAUSE OFFERING STANDARD
MEDICAL TREATMENT TO A PATIENT

23:18.208 --> 23:20.041
IS CLEARLY EMASCULATING.

23:20.083 --> 23:22.041
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU'RE NOT
ALLOWED TO DEFEND HER.

23:22.083 --> 23:24.041
THAT'S AGAINST THE RULES.
YOU GUYS HAVE RULES?

23:24.083 --> 23:26.291
ALL GUYS HAVE RULES, DUDE.
AND HE THINKS
CHARLOTTE HAS THE PROBLEM.

23:26.333 --> 23:28.458
HEY. HEY.
HEY. HEY.

23:28.500 --> 23:30.792
HEY.
DON'T "HEY" ME.

23:30.834 --> 23:33.000
♪ ...IT IN MY EYES ♪

23:33.041 --> 23:36.291
THIS IS WHAT YOU GUYS
DO FOR FUN, HUH?

23:36.333 --> 23:39.583
(wheelchair beeps)
WHAT, SO WHAT,
NOW YOU'RE LEAVING?

23:39.625 --> 23:41.625
I'M MOVING ON.

23:41.667 --> 23:43.041
(mutters)

23:43.083 --> 23:45.208
♪ ...SEEN IT IN YOUR EYES ♪

23:45.250 --> 23:47.667
WOW. THAT GUY'S
A PIECE OF WORK.

23:47.709 --> 23:49.667
♪ NO ONE WILL EVER DO ♪

23:49.709 --> 23:51.250
WHAT?

23:51.291 --> 23:53.333
I'M JUST DRINKING HERE.

23:53.375 --> 23:55.750
YOU THINK
IT'S MY FAULT, TOO?

23:55.792 --> 23:57.667
I WAS NOT WRONG!

23:57.709 --> 24:00.542
SO WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO SAY
IS THAT I OVERREACTED

24:00.583 --> 24:02.959
AND I WANTED TO PICK A FIGHT?
I'M JUST DRINKING HERE.

24:03.000 --> 24:05.208
OH, MAN. ALL RIGHT.
ANOTHER ROUND?

24:05.250 --> 24:07.208
NO, I'LL PASS.

24:07.250 --> 24:09.875
R--WHY?

24:09.917 --> 24:12.208
I DON'T NEED TO MOVE ON.

24:12.250 --> 24:14.875
♪♪♪

24:14.917 --> 24:16.917
OH, YEAH?
(laughs)

24:20.083 --> 24:23.041
YOU'RE HERE LATE.

24:23.083 --> 24:25.917
AM I AN EMASCULATING BITCH?

24:25.959 --> 24:28.792
I ASSUME THIS ISN'T
A TRICK QUESTION.

24:28.834 --> 24:30.792
(chuckles)
IS THIS A COOPER THING OR--

24:30.834 --> 24:32.291
MY SEX ED SEMINAR

24:32.333 --> 24:34.750
TURNED UP A PATIENT
WITH PROSTATE CANCER.

24:34.792 --> 24:37.709
HE'S OLD, THINKS HIS LIFE
WILL BE OVER WITHOUT SEX.

24:37.750 --> 24:39.709
HE WON'T EVEN LISTEN
TO TREATMENT OPTIONS.

24:39.750 --> 24:43.333
AND I THINK I COULD HELP HIM,
BUT HE WON'T TAKE MY CALLS.

24:43.375 --> 24:45.959
COOPER THINKS
I DON'T UNDERSTAND MEN.

24:46.000 --> 24:48.000
I THINK YOU KNOW
HE'S WRONG.

24:49.917 --> 24:52.000
WE THERAPISTS ARE GOOD

24:52.041 --> 24:54.041
AT HELPING PEOPLE
TALK THROUGH THEIR PROBLEMS.

24:54.083 --> 24:55.166
(laughs)

24:55.208 --> 24:57.750
I DON'T LIKE TALKING.

24:57.792 --> 25:02.083
YEAH, WELL,
MAYBE THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.

25:02.125 --> 25:05.625
THINGS I TELL YOU
ARE PRIVILEGED?

25:05.667 --> 25:07.417
OF COURSE.

25:12.417 --> 25:15.834
ADDISON'S PATIENT,
THE ONE IN THE COMA...

25:15.875 --> 25:18.917
I LEFT HER HUSBAND
ALONE IN THE ROOM.

25:18.959 --> 25:20.208
I KNEW HE MIGHT...

25:20.250 --> 25:22.917
END THINGS.

25:22.959 --> 25:24.667
WHY'D YOU DO IT?

25:27.083 --> 25:30.041
WELL, HE WAS THERE...

25:30.083 --> 25:34.000
STARING AT A WOMAN
WHO WOULDN'T WAKE UP.

25:34.041 --> 25:36.041
IT SEEMED SO CRUEL.

25:36.083 --> 25:38.166
I'M BACKING A SURGERY
TO SAVE HER.

25:38.208 --> 25:42.041
THREE BABIES ARE AT RISK.

25:42.083 --> 25:46.041
I'M PUTTING MY FAITH
IN SOME 20-YEAR-OLD KID

25:46.083 --> 25:47.792
BECAUSE I...

25:47.834 --> 25:50.041
BECAUSE YOU WANTED
FORGIVENESS.

25:50.083 --> 25:52.834
I WANT TO BELIEVE
I DIDN'T DO THE WRONG THING

25:52.875 --> 25:54.250
FOR THE WRONG REASONS.

25:54.291 --> 25:56.041
WELL, MAYBE

25:56.083 --> 25:58.834
YOU DID THE WRONG THING
FOR THE RIGHT REASON.

25:58.875 --> 26:01.000
THIS THING
WITH ME AND COOPER...

26:03.083 --> 26:06.041
WHY DID YOU
PUSH ME BACK TO HIM?

26:06.083 --> 26:09.125
BECAUSE IT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

26:18.542 --> 26:20.041
(keys jangle, lock clicks)

26:20.083 --> 26:21.625
HEY.
HEY.

26:21.667 --> 26:23.625
WHEN DID I BECOME THE MAN

26:23.667 --> 26:25.625
OTHER MEN
TELL THEIR PROBLEMS TO?

26:25.667 --> 26:28.500
COULD YOU TELL ME THAT?
MAYBE THE QUESTION IS,

26:28.542 --> 26:31.250
WHEN DID ALL THE MEN I KNOW
BECOME WOMEN?

26:31.291 --> 26:34.709
BECAUSE REALLY, IT'S--
YOU KNOW WHAT? AMELIA IS
GONNA OPERATE ON KAYLA.

26:34.750 --> 26:37.667
OKAY.
AND SHE THINKS I'M SETTLING.
I'M NOT SETTLING.

26:37.709 --> 26:40.458
ARE YOU MAD?
YES, I'M MAD. I'M MAD.

26:40.500 --> 26:43.291
YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT IT'S ABOUT?

26:45.083 --> 26:46.542
(exhales)

26:46.583 --> 26:49.083
YOU SAID,
"I LOVE YOU, VIOLET."

26:49.125 --> 26:51.208
TO ME. YOU SAID IT TO ME.

26:51.250 --> 26:53.041
I--WHAT? I SAID--

26:53.083 --> 26:55.041
WHEN YOU WERE SICK
AND YOU HAD A FEVER,

26:55.083 --> 26:57.041
AND I KNOW
IT SHOULDN'T UPSET ME.

26:57.083 --> 26:59.291
BUT, YOU KNOW, I'M--
I'M HERE BABYSITTING...

26:59.333 --> 27:02.041
PLAYING PEEKABOO
WITH YOUR KID, YOU KNOW?

27:02.083 --> 27:04.417
AND I--YOU SAID,
"I LOVE YOU, VIOLET."
YEAH,
THAT WAS SIX WEEKS AGO.

27:04.458 --> 27:07.458
YOU BEEN CARRYING THIS AROUND
FOR SIX WEEKS?
I'M BUSY. I HAVE A JOB.

27:07.500 --> 27:10.250
I RUN A PRACTICE. I HAVE
THINGS TO DO-- (inhales deeply)

27:10.291 --> 27:12.166
I'M TRYING, OKAY?

27:12.208 --> 27:15.166
I'M TRYING HERE, PETE,
AND I JUST NEED TO KNOW IF--

27:15.208 --> 27:17.166
IF YOU...
DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.

27:17.208 --> 27:20.000
THEN--THEN I WON'T GET
TOO ATTACHED.

27:20.041 --> 27:22.000
BABE, I WILL
ALWAYS LOVE VIOLET.

27:22.041 --> 27:24.917
SHE'S THE MOTHER
OF MY CHILD.
OKAY.

27:24.959 --> 27:27.166
GOOD. I'M GLAD
THAT WE CLEARED THAT UP
SO--NO--

27:27.208 --> 27:29.250
SO I CAN GET MY--
OKAY, ADDISON, ADDISON.

27:29.291 --> 27:32.041
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
I DON'T LOVE YOU.

27:32.083 --> 27:33.667
(chuckles)
MM. I LOVE YOU.

27:33.709 --> 27:35.709
I LOVE YOU.

27:35.750 --> 27:38.375
I'M NOT SITTING AROUND
WAITING FOR VIOLET.

27:38.417 --> 27:42.291
I HAVE MOVED ON,
AND I'M HAPPY I'VE MOVED ON.

27:42.333 --> 27:43.166
YEAH?

27:43.208 --> 27:45.959
YEAH.

27:48.333 --> 27:49.750
(laughs) OKAY.

27:49.792 --> 27:51.000
OKAY?

27:51.041 --> 27:52.291
YEAH.

27:52.333 --> 27:53.208
MM.

27:53.250 --> 27:54.208
MM.

27:54.250 --> 27:55.208
MM.

27:55.250 --> 27:56.208
MM.

27:56.250 --> 27:58.583
(Lucas fusses)
MM.

27:58.625 --> 28:00.041
(fussing ends)

28:00.083 --> 28:02.041
MM.

28:08.083 --> 28:11.333
ARE YOU HERE TO TALK ME
OUT OF THIS AGAIN? BECAUSE--

28:11.375 --> 28:14.000
I'M HERE FOR MY PATIENTS.

28:16.917 --> 28:20.208
VENTRICULOSCOPE IS IN PLACE...

28:20.250 --> 28:24.208
AND I'M MOVING DOWN
TO THE AQUEDUCT.

28:24.250 --> 28:26.375
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

28:26.417 --> 28:29.875
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

28:29.917 --> 28:32.625
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.
KEEP GOING.

28:32.667 --> 28:36.667
ALL RIGHT.
I AM IN THE AQUEDUCT.

28:36.709 --> 28:38.792
GUIDE IS IN PLACE.

28:38.834 --> 28:40.125
PREPARING THE STENT.

28:40.166 --> 28:43.375
ALMOST THERE.

28:43.417 --> 28:47.250
(monitor beeping erratically)
ALL RIGHT, HEART RATE'S UP
TO 130. 140.

28:47.291 --> 28:50.041
SHE'S DESATURATING.
SHE'S THROWN ANOTHER CLOT.

28:50.083 --> 28:52.250
I'M GONNA KEEP GOING.

28:52.291 --> 28:54.166
THE BABIES
ARE IN DISTRESS. SAM.

28:54.208 --> 28:56.917
ALL RIGHT. I'LL NEED TIME
TO REMOVE THE CLOT.

28:56.959 --> 28:59.417
(fetal heart monitor
beeping erratically)

28:59.458 --> 29:01.500
FETAL HEART RATES
ARE IN THE 80s.

29:01.542 --> 29:03.875
LET'S PREP THE BELLY.
I'M CUTTING HER OPEN.

29:03.917 --> 29:06.166
AMELIA, STEP BACK.
I CAN DO THIS, ADDISON.

29:06.208 --> 29:09.166
JUST GIVE SAM A CHANCE.
SO LONG AS THE BABIES
ARE IN THERE,

29:09.208 --> 29:10.834
SHE'S GONNA
KEEP THROWING CLOTS,

29:10.875 --> 29:12.458
AND THEY WILL NOT SURVIVE
THE PROCEDURE.

29:12.500 --> 29:14.041
I NEED
TO DELIVER THE BABIES NOW.

29:14.083 --> 29:20.875
AMELIA, STEP BACK.
SCALPEL.

29:25.583 --> 29:27.041
BABY NUMBER ONE.

29:27.083 --> 29:30.750
CALL NICU. GET THREE VENTS
AND A CENTRAL LINE SET UP.

29:30.792 --> 29:32.625
(woman speaks indistinctly)

29:32.667 --> 29:35.208
BABY NUMBER TWO. COME ON.

29:35.250 --> 29:36.542
(monitor beeping erratically)

29:36.583 --> 29:39.667
WHY WASN'T I PAGED?
I HAVE A FULL TEAM HERE.

29:39.709 --> 29:43.208
I'M AN ATTENDING ON THIS CASE.
YOU COULD'VE USED ME.

29:43.250 --> 29:45.250
NUMBER THREE.
SAM, YOU'RE CLEAR TO GO.

29:45.291 --> 29:47.709
SHE'S FLOPPY.
NO SPONTANEOUS RESPIRATION.

29:47.750 --> 29:49.041
I CAN'T FEEL A HEARTBEAT.

29:49.083 --> 29:52.500
LET ME ASSIST YOU.
I'VE GOT IT.
SET UP AN INTUBATION TRAY.

29:52.542 --> 29:55.000
LET ME HELP YOU.
WE ARE HERE
BECAUSE OF YOU.

29:55.041 --> 29:58.041
THIS BABY IS LIKE THIS
BECAUSE OF YOU.

29:58.083 --> 30:01.250
THE BEST THING YOU CAN DO
RIGHT NOW IS BACK OFF.

30:01.291 --> 30:03.250
GIVE ME AN E.T. TUBE.

30:03.291 --> 30:05.166
ALL RIGHT. SUCTION.
SHE'S ASPIRATED.

30:05.208 --> 30:07.166
IS SHE ALL RIGHT?

30:07.208 --> 30:09.667
OKAY, I'M ALMOST THERE.
ALMOST THERE. GOT IT.

30:09.709 --> 30:13.250
OKAY. HOLD C.P.R.
(monitor beeping erratically)

30:13.291 --> 30:15.166
THERE'S NO PULSE.
RESUME C.P.R.

30:15.208 --> 30:17.583
OKAY.

30:17.625 --> 30:18.917
(air whooshes)

30:18.959 --> 30:20.792
(whoosh)

30:20.834 --> 30:21.792
(whoosh)

30:21.834 --> 30:23.041
COME ON.

30:23.083 --> 30:24.291
(whoosh)

30:24.333 --> 30:26.625
COME ON.

30:26.667 --> 30:28.834
COME ON, BABY.
HOLD ON.

30:28.875 --> 30:30.291
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

30:30.333 --> 30:33.041
GOOD. WE GOT A RHYTHM...
AND A PULSE.

30:33.083 --> 30:35.041
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GET HER INTO NICU.

30:35.083 --> 30:37.583
CALL AN ECMO UNIT. THIS BABY
NEEDS TO BE ON BYPASS.

30:37.625 --> 30:41.291
HAVE THE TECHS MEET US
AT THE UNIT. LET'S GO.
IS SHE GONNA BE OKAY?

30:41.333 --> 30:43.375
SAM, YOU GOT THIS?
YEAH.

30:43.417 --> 30:44.792
(monitor beeps erratically)

30:44.834 --> 30:47.125
(Oscar) APPARENTLY,
YOU'VE SPOKEN TO DR. KING.

30:47.166 --> 30:48.375
YES.

30:48.417 --> 30:49.834
I TOLD HER

30:49.875 --> 30:52.375
THAT YOU HAD THE RIGHT
TO REFUSE MEDICAL TREATMENT,

30:52.417 --> 30:54.375
WHICH IS TRUE.
THANK YOU.

30:54.417 --> 30:56.583
BUT I ALSO THINK
IT'S WRONG.

30:56.625 --> 30:58.041
IMPOTENCE IS NOT

30:58.083 --> 31:00.458
AN INEVITABLE SIDE EFFECT
OF RADIATION.

31:00.500 --> 31:03.375
SHE SAID I HAVE
A 50/50 CHANCE

31:03.417 --> 31:05.250
OF LOSING FUNCTION.

31:05.291 --> 31:08.166
AND IF YOU COME DOWN
ON THE WRONG SIDE OF THAT,

31:08.208 --> 31:11.166
YOU STILL HAVE
A WOMAN THAT LOVES YOU.
BUT I WON'T BE ABLE
TO LOVE HER BACK.

31:11.208 --> 31:14.166
WELL, MAYBE NOT IN THE WAY
THAT YOU CAN NOW.

31:14.208 --> 31:16.166
BUT WITH THE HELP
OF DR. KING...

31:16.208 --> 31:17.959
IT'S NOT THE SAME.

31:18.000 --> 31:20.667
WELL, YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT WOULD BE DIFFERENT.

31:20.709 --> 31:24.458
BUT THESE OPTIONS
THAT DR. KING MENTIONED,

31:24.500 --> 31:27.834
THEY DON'T HAVE TO...

31:27.875 --> 31:30.041
THEY DON'T MAKE YOU
LESS OF A MAN.

31:30.083 --> 31:33.625
YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO GET OLD?

31:33.667 --> 31:35.834
PEOPLE START DOING THINGS
FOR YOU.

31:35.875 --> 31:39.792
THEY STOP LETTING YOU
DO THINGS FOR YOURSELF...

31:39.834 --> 31:42.041
LIKE WORK A JOB, UH,

31:42.083 --> 31:44.041
OR LIVE IN A HOUSE

31:44.083 --> 31:48.000
OR DRIVE YOUR OWN CAR
DOWN THE STREET.

31:48.041 --> 31:49.291
I LOST MY WIFE.

31:49.333 --> 31:52.041
MY KIDS
HAVE LIVES OF THEIR OWN.

31:52.083 --> 31:53.834
I'M STUCK HERE.

31:53.875 --> 31:58.041
BUT THERE'S ONE THING THAT
I CAN STILL DO FOR MYSELF,

31:58.083 --> 32:01.083
ONE THING THAT MAKES ME
FEEL WHOLE.

32:01.125 --> 32:04.041
AND I'M NOT ABOUT
TO LET THAT BE TAKEN AWAY

32:04.083 --> 32:08.000
OR--OR HAVE IT MADE
UNCOMFORTABLE OR UNNATURAL.

32:11.083 --> 32:14.041
WELL, I ADMIT I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE TO GET OLD.

32:14.083 --> 32:17.834
AND WHEN IT COMES TO SEX,
I GET THAT.

32:17.875 --> 32:19.417
AND WHEN...

32:19.458 --> 32:21.917
YOU CAN'T DO IT...

32:21.959 --> 32:25.417
I MEAN, THAT IS...

32:25.458 --> 32:28.875
LOOK, IT HAPPENS.
IT HAPPENS TO EVERY GUY.

32:28.917 --> 32:31.041
I...

32:31.083 --> 32:33.041
I WAS WITH A WOMAN I LOVED,

32:33.083 --> 32:35.834
AND WE WERE FIGHTING A LOT,

32:35.875 --> 32:38.875
AND, UH... I WAS STRESSED OUT,

32:38.917 --> 32:44.000
AND THAT MADE IT
DIFFICULT... TO PERFORM.

32:46.083 --> 32:48.041
AND IT WAS HUMILIATING.

32:48.083 --> 32:50.041
OH... IT WAS.

32:50.083 --> 32:52.000
AND SO I PUSHED HER AWAY

32:52.041 --> 32:54.458
AND I TREATED HER BADLY

32:54.500 --> 32:57.458
BECAUSE I WAS FEELING LIKE
I WAS LESS OF A MAN.

32:57.500 --> 32:59.125
I WAS... I WAS WRONG.

32:59.166 --> 33:02.333
I WAS JUST WRONG.

33:02.375 --> 33:04.500
MR. SCHMITT,
I CAN'T PROMISE YOU

33:04.542 --> 33:06.500
THAT THERE'LL BE
NO SIDE EFFECTS

33:06.542 --> 33:08.500
IF YOU DO THIS TREATMENT.

33:08.542 --> 33:11.041
BUT I DO KNOW
THAT YOU'LL BE ALIVE

33:11.083 --> 33:15.041
AND YOU WILL GET TO CONTINUE
TO LOVE NORA

33:15.083 --> 33:18.041
FOR A LONG TIME TO COME.

33:18.083 --> 33:21.041
YOU WILL BE
THE MAN IN HER LIFE.

33:21.083 --> 33:23.750
AND THAT'S
THE MOST IMPORTANT THING.

33:31.083 --> 33:33.041
(monitor beeping erratically)

33:33.083 --> 33:34.166
SAM.

33:34.208 --> 33:38.041
ALMOST THERE. 30cc SYRINGE.

33:38.083 --> 33:41.166
(beeping continues)

33:41.208 --> 33:45.333
AND CLOTS ARE DISSOLVING.

33:45.375 --> 33:47.458
VITALS ARE STABILIZING.

33:47.500 --> 33:50.834
THE REST IS UP TO YOU,
DR. SHEPHERD.

33:50.875 --> 33:52.625
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

33:52.667 --> 33:55.041
I ALMOST KILLED HER, SAM.

33:55.083 --> 33:56.792
AND THOSE BABIES--

33:56.834 --> 33:59.875
THEY'RE IN ADDISON'S HANDS.

33:59.917 --> 34:02.417
(whispers)
WHAT AM I DOING?

34:02.458 --> 34:06.041
YOU'RE A DOING SURGERY
ON A WOMAN'S BRAIN...

34:06.083 --> 34:08.041
A-A SURGERY YOU SAID
ONLY YOU COULD DO...

34:08.083 --> 34:10.041
A SURGERY YOU FOUGHT FOR.

34:10.083 --> 34:12.333
STOP STANDING THERE AND START
ACTING LIKE A SURGEON.

34:12.375 --> 34:14.333
(normal voice)
YOU SOUND LIKE ADDISON.

34:14.375 --> 34:15.792
NO, I SOUND LIKE YOU

34:15.834 --> 34:18.125
BEFORE YOU STARTED
LOSING CONFIDENCE IN YOURSELF.

34:18.166 --> 34:19.583
AMELIA, CAN YOU DO THIS?

34:19.625 --> 34:20.500
CAN YOU WAKE THIS WOMAN UP

34:20.542 --> 34:22.500
AND BRING HER BACK
TO HER FAMILY?

34:22.542 --> 34:25.417
OR WERE JUST SPOUTING
A BUNCH OF MESS

34:25.458 --> 34:27.458
BECAUSE YOU LIKE TO CUT?

34:27.500 --> 34:31.709
(exhales deeply)

34:31.750 --> 34:32.792
I CAN DO THIS.

34:32.834 --> 34:35.417
OKAY, THEN. GO.
WE DON'T HAVE ALL DAY.

34:35.458 --> 34:37.458
ADJUST THE SCOPE. SET UP
THE CATHETER FOR THE STENT.

34:37.500 --> 34:39.667
LET'S SHOW YOUR BROTHER
HE'S NOT THE ONLY SHEPHERD

34:39.709 --> 34:44.000
WHO CAN MAKE MAGIC.

34:44.041 --> 34:45.417
ATTAGIRL.

34:48.083 --> 34:49.834
(Amelia) IT DIDN'T WORK.

34:49.875 --> 34:51.500
(Sam) YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

34:51.542 --> 34:53.000
THE OTHER PATIENTS

34:53.041 --> 34:55.041
WERE AT LEAST
MARGINALLY RESPONSIVE BY NOW.

34:55.083 --> 34:57.041
I FREAKED OUT, SAM.

34:57.083 --> 34:58.458
MAYBE I TOOK TOO LONG.

34:58.500 --> 35:01.041
MAYBE I SHOULD'VE STOPPED.
MAYBE ADDISON WAS--

35:01.083 --> 35:04.041
SHE'S IN PAIN.
IS THAT GOOD OR BAD?

35:04.083 --> 35:05.875
(woman)
♪ WAIT A MINUTE HERE ♪

35:05.917 --> 35:08.917
(moans)

35:08.959 --> 35:11.875
♪ LET'S JUST MAKE IT CLEAR,
TO THE END... ♪

35:11.917 --> 35:14.041
THAT'S NOT A PAIN RESPONSE.

35:14.083 --> 35:15.875
(moans)
WHOA. NEITHER IS THAT.

35:15.917 --> 35:17.041
SWEETHEART?

35:17.083 --> 35:18.667
PUPILS ARE EQUAL
AND REACTIVE.

35:18.709 --> 35:21.875
POSITIVE DOLL'S EYE RESPONSE.
(Eddie) IS SHE WAKING UP?

35:21.917 --> 35:23.750
(moans)

35:23.792 --> 35:26.500
HER BRAIN STEM REFLEXES
ARE IMPROVING.

35:26.542 --> 35:28.542
SHE'S WAKING UP?
(Amelia) SHE'S WAKING UP.

35:28.583 --> 35:31.125
BABY?
SHE'S WAKING UP.

35:31.166 --> 35:32.917
(Kayla moans)

35:32.959 --> 35:34.792
SHE'S WAKING UP.

35:34.834 --> 35:37.959
APPLICATION LOOKS GOOD.
I'M SENDING IT IN.

35:38.000 --> 35:40.583
OF COURSE IT LOOKS GOOD.
I WROTE IT.

35:40.625 --> 35:43.333
♪ IT'S JUST YOU AND ME ♪
♪ AND ME ♪

35:43.375 --> 35:45.333
THAT WAS
SOME PRETTY GOOD GAME

35:45.375 --> 35:47.250
YOU WERE THROWING LAST NIGHT.

35:47.291 --> 35:49.041
YOU GET HER NUMBER?

35:49.083 --> 35:51.041
YEAH, I GOT HER NUMBER.

35:51.083 --> 35:53.041
GONNA CALL HER?

35:53.083 --> 35:55.083
(laughs)
I DON'T THINK SO.

35:55.125 --> 35:56.458
WHY?

35:56.500 --> 35:58.750
NOT INTERESTED.

35:58.792 --> 36:01.250
NOT READY TO MOVE ON?

36:01.291 --> 36:05.083
NAOMI WILL COME BACK.
I'M GOING TO WAIT.

36:05.125 --> 36:08.208
♪ YOU CAN GO ABOUT YOUR WAY ♪

36:08.250 --> 36:11.041
♪ NOT WHILE I AM HERE ♪

36:11.083 --> 36:12.583
ADDISON.

36:12.625 --> 36:14.792
IT WORKED. I WAS RIGHT.

36:14.834 --> 36:17.041
NO. NO, YOU WERE NOT RIGHT.

36:17.083 --> 36:19.208
YOU OVERREACHED
AND YOU OVERSTEPPED

36:19.250 --> 36:22.000
AND YOU FORCED ME TO TAKE OUT
THOSE BABIES WAY TOO EARLY.

36:22.041 --> 36:24.000
THEY ALL COULD'VE DIED.
BUT THEY'RE OKAY.

36:24.041 --> 36:27.000
THEY SURVIVED. THEY'RE STABLE,
AT LEAST FOR NOW.

36:27.041 --> 36:29.083
BUT DON'T KID YOURSELF.
YOU GOT LUCKY IN THERE.

36:29.125 --> 36:32.041
NO, THAT WASN'T--
YOU COULD BE A GREAT SURGEON.

36:32.083 --> 36:35.041
BUT RIGHT NOW, YOU'RE NOT HALF
AS GOOD AS YOU THINK YOU ARE,

36:35.083 --> 36:37.041
AND I SAY THAT AS A DOCTOR

36:37.083 --> 36:39.125
WITH FAR MORE EXPERIENCE
THAN YOU.

36:39.166 --> 36:42.000
♪ NOW ALL I CAN SEE,
IT'S JUST YOU AND ME ♪

36:42.041 --> 36:44.041
♪ AND ME ♪
♪ JUST YOU AND ME ♪

36:44.083 --> 36:46.000
BUT AS...

36:46.041 --> 36:47.208
YOUR SISTER-IN-LAW--

36:47.250 --> 36:50.875
YOUR FORMER...
SISTER-IN-LAW--

36:50.917 --> 36:52.792
LOOK AT THAT.

36:52.834 --> 36:54.041
SHE'S UP, SHE'S AWAKE.

36:54.083 --> 36:56.667
THAT'S A FAMILY,
AND YOU DID THAT.

36:56.709 --> 36:59.959
THOSE KIDS HAVE A MOTHER.
HE'S GOT THE WOMAN HE LOVES.

37:00.000 --> 37:02.041
SO... CELEBRATE THAT,

37:02.083 --> 37:05.041
'CAUSE IT'S A MIRACLE.

37:05.083 --> 37:07.041
♪♪♪

37:07.083 --> 37:09.834
I'M GLAD TO SEE YOU BOTH
BACK HERE.

37:09.875 --> 37:13.458
I DECIDED TO GO
WITH THE TREATMENT.

37:13.500 --> 37:15.041
NORA AND I, UH...

37:15.083 --> 37:18.041
WE JUST CAME IN TO GET
SOME ADVICE FOR AFTER.

37:18.083 --> 37:21.083
I'M GLAD.
WHY DON'T YOU TWO
GET SETTLED INSIDE?

37:21.125 --> 37:25.041
I'LL BE IN
IN A MINUTE.

37:25.083 --> 37:26.375
(whispers) THANK YOU...

37:26.417 --> 37:29.041
(normal voice)
FOR TALKING TO HIM,

37:29.083 --> 37:31.041
FOR GETTING HIM
TO COME BACK.

37:31.083 --> 37:34.041
YEAH, I'M--I'M SORRY.
I WAS AN ASS TO YOU.

37:34.083 --> 37:35.041
YEAH.

37:35.083 --> 37:36.041
(laughs)

37:36.083 --> 37:37.875
YOU WERE.

37:37.917 --> 37:40.041
BUT MAYBE WE CAN
WORK TOGETHER AFTER ALL

37:40.083 --> 37:42.125
AND NOT KILL EACH OTHER.

37:42.166 --> 37:46.500
MAYBE WE CAN.
I'M GONNA GO DO WORK.

37:46.542 --> 37:51.083
HEY, WHAT DO YOU SAY
TO A DRINK AFTER WORK?

37:51.125 --> 37:53.875
I DON'T THINK SO.

37:53.917 --> 37:56.750
YOU AFRAID
TO BE FRIENDS, COOPER?

37:56.792 --> 38:00.041
I'M NOT AFRAID.

38:00.083 --> 38:02.041
THEN WHAT?

38:02.083 --> 38:04.291
♪ IT'S JUST YOU AND ME ♪
♪ AND ME ♪

38:04.333 --> 38:06.083
I DON'T KNOW.

38:06.125 --> 38:08.083
♪ AND ME ♪
♪ JUST YOU AND ME ♪

38:08.125 --> 38:10.500
♪ AND ME ♪

38:10.542 --> 38:15.250
♪ TILL WE SOMEHOW FOUND RELIEF ♪

38:15.291 --> 38:17.709
(babies crying)

38:17.750 --> 38:19.667
HEY. BIG WIN.

38:19.709 --> 38:22.166
KAYLA'S AWAKE.
THE BABIES SURVIVED.

38:22.208 --> 38:24.792
GOOD STUFF, HUH?

38:24.834 --> 38:26.333
OH.

38:26.375 --> 38:29.250
LOOK AT HOW MUCH
HE LOVES HER.

38:29.291 --> 38:32.291
GOD,
THEY'VE BEEN THROUGH HELL.

38:32.333 --> 38:35.333
AND NO MATTER HOW IT TURNS OUT,
THEY HAVE EACH OTHER.

38:35.375 --> 38:38.041
THAT'S HOW
THEY GOT THROUGH THIS.

38:38.083 --> 38:41.041
MM-HMM. (sips)

38:41.083 --> 38:43.333
WHY DIDN'T YOU
STAND UP FOR ME?

38:43.375 --> 38:45.333
IN THE O.R. WITH ADDISON--

38:45.375 --> 38:48.959
SHE SHUT ME OUT,
AND YOU DIDN'T SAY A WORD.

38:49.000 --> 38:50.709
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

38:50.750 --> 38:53.208
(whispers, voice breaking)
IF YOU'RE SLEEPING WITH ADDISON,

38:53.250 --> 38:55.041
SAY IT.

38:55.083 --> 38:56.750
W--

38:56.792 --> 38:59.750
(sighs) IF I'M JUST
A PIT STOP, SAY IT.

38:59.792 --> 39:01.834
VANESSA, PLEASE--
(normal voice)
STOP WASTING MY TIME.

39:01.875 --> 39:03.750
ADDISON IS NOT
A FACTOR HERE.

39:03.792 --> 39:06.041
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

39:06.083 --> 39:08.333
(sighs)

39:08.375 --> 39:10.417
(whispers)
DO YOU LOVE HER?

39:10.458 --> 39:13.667
(babies continue crying)

39:16.083 --> 39:19.625
(voice breaks)
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

39:21.583 --> 39:24.583
(The Rescues' "Follow Me
Back Into the Sun" playing)

39:27.250 --> 39:30.208
HOW IS IT THAT A WOMAN
CAN BE WOKEN UP FROM THE DEAD

39:30.250 --> 39:34.041
AND I CAN'T EVEN BE FRIENDS
WITH COOPER?
ADDISON'S PATIENT WOKE UP?

39:34.083 --> 39:37.041
YEAH. CRAZY, RIGHT?
WELL, MAYBE YOU DID
THE RIGHT THING AFTER ALL.

39:37.083 --> 39:40.041
SEE, I-I TOLD YOU.
NO, I DID THE WRONG THING WITH
HER, AND IT TURNED OUT OKAY.

39:40.083 --> 39:42.041
I DID THE WRONG THING
WITH COOPER,

39:42.083 --> 39:45.250
AND IT TURNED OUT BADLY.
(sighs) STILL NO WORD
FROM YOUR PATIENT?

39:45.291 --> 39:47.875
THE OPPOSITE.
COOPER GOT HIM TO COME IN.

39:47.917 --> 39:50.583
HE AGREED TO DO TREATMENT.

39:50.625 --> 39:53.125
THEN HE WOULDN'T EVEN
HAVE A DRINK WITH ME.

39:53.166 --> 39:55.375
BUT YOU WORKED TOGETHER
WITH GOOD RESULTS. RIGHT?

39:55.417 --> 39:57.875
I MEAN, IT'S A START.

39:57.917 --> 40:00.667
STOP GETTING MY HOPES UP.

40:00.709 --> 40:05.417
HOW LONG DID THAT MAN WAIT
FOR HIS WIFE TO WAKE UP?

40:05.458 --> 40:07.583
(sighs)
AH, HE'LL COME AROUND.

40:07.625 --> 40:10.583
IN THE MEANTIME,
YOU COME HAVE A DRINK WITH ME.

40:10.625 --> 40:13.583
I MEAN, YOU AND COOPER
MIGHT NOT BE THERE YET,

40:13.625 --> 40:15.792
BUT YOU AND I
CAN STILL BE FRIENDS, RIGHT?

40:15.834 --> 40:17.583
(laughs) RIGHT?

40:17.625 --> 40:20.917
(laughs) YES.

40:20.959 --> 40:22.458
(babbles)

40:22.500 --> 40:24.625
AHH. MMM.

40:24.667 --> 40:26.583
HEY.

40:26.625 --> 40:28.208
OH, THERE YOU ARE.

40:28.250 --> 40:30.083
OH.

40:30.125 --> 40:32.041
THANK YOU...

40:32.083 --> 40:35.041
FOR LETTING ME
STAY HERE TONIGHT.

40:35.083 --> 40:37.834
AMELIA IS AT MY HOUSE,
AND I JUST...

40:37.875 --> 40:41.041
JUST WANTED IT TO BE...
US TONIGHT--

40:41.083 --> 40:45.041
JUST YOU, ME...
AND LUCAS.

40:45.083 --> 40:46.625
THAT SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

40:46.667 --> 40:48.041
HEY.

40:48.083 --> 40:49.625
YOU OKAY?

40:49.667 --> 40:51.041
YEAH. YEAH.

40:51.083 --> 40:52.625
HI, BABY.

40:52.667 --> 40:54.041
(babbles)

40:54.083 --> 40:55.667
OH. (laughs)

40:55.709 --> 40:58.083
KAYLA WOKE UP.

40:58.125 --> 41:00.917
WOW.
THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

41:00.959 --> 41:02.542
♪ ...TIME ♪

41:02.583 --> 41:04.542
YEAH, YEAH, IT IS.

41:04.583 --> 41:06.291
♪ FOR FOREVER TO COME ♪

41:06.333 --> 41:09.041
♪ I'M RIGHT BEHIND YOU ♪

41:09.083 --> 41:10.542
MM.

41:10.583 --> 41:12.500
♪ DON'T KNOW
HOW TO LEAVE YOU ♪

41:12.542 --> 41:15.041
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

41:15.083 --> 41:17.750
(makes popping sound)
(Pete and Addison laugh)

41:17.792 --> 41:19.750
(doorbell rings)
OH, I ORDERED US
SOME CHINESE.

41:19.792 --> 41:21.917
MMM. YUM.

41:21.959 --> 41:24.583
HI, BUDDY.

41:24.625 --> 41:26.041
(whispers) HI.

41:26.083 --> 41:28.041
(normal voice) OKAY.
READY? OHH.

41:28.083 --> 41:30.041
(coughs)
OOH.

41:30.083 --> 41:32.000
(Addison laughs)

41:32.041 --> 41:35.041
♪ LEAVE YOU NOW ♪
♪ IN THE CORNER OF MY EYE ♪

41:35.083 --> 41:37.041
♪ DON'T KNOW HOW TO... ♪

41:37.083 --> 41:39.208
HI.

41:39.250 --> 41:43.709
♪ DON'T KNOW
HOW TO LEAVE YOU NOW ♪

41:43.750 --> 41:44.625
VIOLET.

41:44.667 --> 41:47.500
♪ LEAVE YOU NOW ♪
♪ I SEE... ♪

41:47.542 --> 41:50.375
I, UH, I CAME
STRAIGHT FROM THE AIRPORT.

41:50.417 --> 41:52.792
AND...

41:52.834 --> 41:57.625
♪ DON'T KNOW
HOW TO LEAVE YOU NOW ♪

41:57.667 --> 41:59.792
♪ LEAVE YOU NOW ♪

41:59.834 --> 42:01.667
U-UH...

42:01.709 --> 42:05.041
♪ NOW ♪

42:05.083 --> 42:07.291
♪ OH ♪

42:07.333 --> 42:10.208
♪ YEAH, YEAH ♪

42:10.250 --> 42:13.166
♪ LEAVE YOU NOW ♪

42:13.208 --> 42:15.333
I WANT TO SEE LUCAS.

42:15.375 --> 42:18.250
♪♪♪

42:21.083 --> 42:22.250
(Lucas coos)

42:22.291 --> 42:25.250
♪♪♪
